<title>UK: GOLF-LANGER'S ITALIAN VICTORY HELPS RETAIN TOP 20 PLACE.</title>
<headline>GOLF-LANGER'S ITALIAN VICTORY HELPS RETAIN TOP 20 PLACE.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bernhard Langer's victory in the</p>
<p>Italian Open on Sunday has lifted him from 20th position to 16th</p>
<p>in the lastest world rankings issued on Monday.</p>
<p>The German is one of only two players to have retained a</p>
<p>place in the world top 20 since the rankings began in 1986 --</p>
<p>the other is world number one Greg Norman who has never been</p>
<p>below seventh in the list.</p>
<p>The top 20 (U.S. unless stated)</p>
<p>1. Greg Norman (Australia)	  10.60 points average</p>
<p>2. Tom Lehman			    9.87</p>
<p>3. Steve Elkington (Australia)     9.00</p>
<p>4. Nick Price (Zimbabwe)	     8.96</p>
<p>5. Tiger Woods			   8.73</p>
<p>6. Colin Montgomerie (Britain)     8.68</p>
<p>7. Masashi Ozaki (Japan)	     8.53</p>
<p>8. Ernie Els (South Africa)	  8.37</p>
<p>9. Mark O'Meara			  7.94</p>
<p>10. Phil Mickelson		     7.54</p>
<p>11. Fred Couples			 6.95</p>
<p>12. Nick Faldo (Britain)	     6.64</p>
<p>13. Brad Faxon			   6.56</p>
<p>14. Scott Hoch			   6.56</p>
